text:
Believe it or not, it's been proven that positive and negative affirmations work. If you tell yourself "I'm ugly" "I'm fat" "I'm not good enough" that's all you will ever believe. I mean why would you believe any different? The person you spend 24/7 with (yourself) is adamant you aren't beautiful so of course you are going to feel it's a lie when you say it in the mirror. 


But you can just as easily change your thinking in the other direction. Its going to feel fake at first but it's not, it's just new. Stick with it. "I am beautiful." "I love my body, I love me." Say that every morning in front of the mirror and I promise you'll start feeling better about yourself within a month. 

Our words and thoughts have power. Don't let anxiety and insecurities take control of the speakers in your head. Try to change what tune is playing
